cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language understanding and inference, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of constrained conditional models (CCMs) and integer linear programming (ILP) also suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with extracting relations from text. Finally, the use of statistical models and inference techniques suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
